= Methodology

== Overview <sec-overview>
We present ABIscope, a novel tool designed to generate user-space test cases for differential analysis of Linux ABI Compatibility in Rust-based kernels targeting syscalls. The overall pipeline follows an iterative seed generation and evaluation process, leveraging LLMs with feedback-driven exploration. At a high level, ABIscope consists of four key stages: (1) Seed initialization (#ref(<sec-seed-initialization>, supplement: [Section])), (2) LLM-based mutation (#ref(<sec-LLM-based-mutation>, supplement: [Section])), (3) execution and validation (#ref(<sec-Execution-and-Validation>, supplement: [Section])), and (4) coverage-guided selection (#ref(<sec-coverage-guided-selection>, supplement: [Section])). These four key components form a closed feedback loop. The overall pipeline is illustrated in #ref(<fig-pipeline>, supplement: [Figure]). We describe each stage in detail in the following sections.

